cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.GRAPHICS, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the use of synthetic imagery in training deep models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a novel learned synthesis technique for rendering synthetic data, which involves graphics (cs.GR) and computer graphics (cs.GRAPHICS). Finally, the paper uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) to generate synthetic data, which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
